Sentencas: The effect of molybdenum addition on the oxidation, electric property and Cr evaporation of Fe-22Cr-0.5Mn ferritic stainless steel is investigated in terms of mass gain, area specific resistance and Cr evaporation rate.
Titulo: Molybdenum effect on oxidation resistance and electric conduction of ferritic stainless steel for SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: Addition of 0.1-2 wt% Mo reduces the oxidation rate and especially area specific resistance of Fe-22Cr-0.5Mn steel.
Titulo: Molybdenum effect on oxidation resistance and electric conduction of ferritic stainless steel for SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: Mo addition of these contents increases the activation energy and suppresses the inward diffusion of oxygen, which indicates the defect chemistry of oxide scale is altered.
Titulo: Molybdenum effect on oxidation resistance and electric conduction of ferritic stainless steel for SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: This results in the increase of oxidation resistance and electric conductivity.
Titulo: Molybdenum effect on oxidation resistance and electric conduction of ferritic stainless steel for SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: When more than 4 wt% Mo is added, the oxidation rate increases after 300 h of oxidation at 800 degrees C in ambient air.
Titulo: Molybdenum effect on oxidation resistance and electric conduction of ferritic stainless steel for SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: The evaporation of volatile Mo species reduces the stability of protective chromia, so that rapid growing Ferich spinel is formed after 300 h of oxidation.
Titulo: Molybdenum effect on oxidation resistance and electric conduction of ferritic stainless steel for SOFC interconnect

Sentencas: The evaporation rate of Cr is similar in all alloys.
Titulo: Molybdenum effect on oxidation resistance and electric conduction of ferritic stainless steel for SOFC interconnect
